SUMMARY:Online Meetup
DESCRIPTION:We’re meeting on Discord! The link to join the Baltimore Indie Game Devs discord server will be in your RSVP message. \nJoin us to discuss game development\, talk shop\, and bounce ideas. Anyone with an interest in game design and development is welcome\, from beginners to veteran professionals. \nIf you’re working on a game\, you’re welcome to show it and ask for feedback. There will be plenty of time to chat and talk shop\, too.
URL:https://baltimoreindiegames.com/event/online-meetup-4/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20250805T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20250805T200000
DTSTAMP:20250721T225237
CREATED:20250705T154803Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20250705T154803Z
UID:206-1754416800-1754424000@baltimoreindiegames.com
SUMMARY:Dev Mode
DESCRIPTION:DevMode is a new gathering for Baltimore-based game developers\, digital artists\, creative technologists\, and tech-minded entrepreneurs to connect\, network\, and spark ideas. Whether you’re building AAA titles\, experimenting in Unreal or Unity\, or exploring how your skills might translate into the gaming space\, this is for YOU. Meet local devs\, test-play featured games\, and mingle with the talent shaping the future of interactive media in Baltimore and beyond. \nDevMode is for: \n\nGame devs\nIndie creators\nTech entrepreneurs\n3D artists & animators\nInteractive media & XR creatives\nAnyone curious about working in game dev\n\nDevMode is FREE to attend. Registration is required in advance or at the door. \nCo-presented by the SNF Parkway Theatre and Game 4 Good\, this laid-back gathering kicks off a new era of gaming-focused community events in Baltimore.
URL:https://baltimoreindiegames.com/event/dev-mode/
LOCATION:Parkway Theatre\, 5 W North Ave\, Baltimore\, MD\, 21201\, United States
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20250816T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20250816T113000
DTSTAMP:20250721T225237
CREATED:20250709T004104Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20250711T181757Z
UID:215-1755338400-1755343800@baltimoreindiegames.com
SUMMARY:In-Person/Online Meetup (Version Control Certification)
DESCRIPTION:In-person is at the East Columbia Branch Library in the Marvin Thomas Room. \nJoin us IN-PERSON or ONLINE. Anyone with an interest in game design and development is welcome\, from beginners to veteran professionals. \nJulian Coy will run a Version Control Basic Proficiency certification session from 10:30 AM – 11:30 AM. Learn how to use version control to work with teams. Great for artists and programmers alike! \nWe will be meeting in the Marvin Thomas Room at the East Columbia Branch Library (6600 Cradlerock Way\, Columbia\, MD). (Not an official Howard County Library System event.) \nIf you want to attend virtually\, the Discord server link is provided in the main monthly (1st of the month) meetup details. An organizer will ensure that a laptop is provided on-site to connect the Discord attendees with those physically on-site. It takes us a few minutes to set up the projector\, so hold tight when you join the Discord voice chat channel. We’ll be there soon!
URL:https://baltimoreindiegames.com/event/in-person-online-meetup-4/
LOCATION:East Columbia Branch
END:VEVENT
